Hey Brent, I’m good, sorry about the late response the app doesn’t notify me when a message is sent.

I’m good, how are you?

A little about my self, I’m currently a second year university student at Norwich University of the arts studying vfx.

In my first year I mainly focused on matte painting and tried to improve myself over the year, later on I realised I love it but it’s not where I want to be for the rest of my life and started looking into other parts of the pipeline.
I slowly started to learn roto and I like doing it when I have time and can just chill, I don’t mind doing a couple of hour of roto if I’m jamming to some good music.

This current year I’m focusing of composition and trying to make that the main aspect of what I want to work as.
I don’t know much but I’m slowly learning and will preserve to understand something if I can’t comprehend it straight away.
Hey wow I know what you mean. No notification.

Currently I am a lead fx artist at Framestore London.  I have been in fx for a out 7 years. Before that I was a generalist.  I have worked in the United States. Australia and now in the UK.
